      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bottle",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Measure the arrowroot powder into the spray bottle first. Add the witch hazel and swirl to combine -- the arrowroot will suspend temporarily. Add the essential oils. Cap and shake well. The arrowroot will settle between uses; shake for 10 seconds before each application.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How to use",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shake vigorously. Hold the bottle 5 to 8 cm from clean, dry underarm skin and spray two to three times. Allow to dry fully before dressing -- the arrowroot can transfer to fabric if applied to damp skin. Apply morning and reapply if needed during the day. The spray works best on freshly washed skin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Managing expectations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is a deodorant, not an antiperspirant. It neutralises odour without blocking sweat glands. Most people switching from aluminium-based antiperspirants experience a 2 to 4 week adjustment period during which sweat output normalises. Effectiveness varies between individuals. If irritation occurs, reduce or omit the tea tree oil.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Storage and shelf life",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Keep at room temperature. Shake before each use. Use within two months. Discard if the spray develops an unusual smell or if the arrowroot clumps and will not re-suspend.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}